9:
Paper talismans, huh? Attacking
with those AND your sword was a bit
too much for me...
11:
But forget that—YOU were incredible
there! Suizen told me how difficult it
is to use those kinds of moves!
15:
...Seek not pleasures of the senses. I
grew up with that commandment,
so all I've known in my life is training.
18:
Seriously? That's... a bit strict. Were
there any other commandments?
21:
Suffer not a yokai to live.
Seek not pleasures of the senses.
War not without cause.
23:
...I always had my doubts about the
commandments.
25:
But all my questioning only made
me feel guilty, and I was never able
to act.
28:
Perhaps... BUT! The commandments
are no more—there is no need to
follow such stuffy rules!
33:
The time has come to do WHATEVER
your heart desires!
37:
Commandments or no, I still need to
keep up my training.
40:
How diligent of you! Luckily, it seems
your training for the day is now over!
44:
This means it is time... to TREAT
yourself and ENTICE your senses! Let
us taste true freedom, Rengetsu!
53:
U-um... Goodness, this is hard. They
all look so delicious.
57:
Then you are within your rights to try
them ALL!
61: But that would be... far too indulgent!
65:
...I'll have strawberry, rum raisin, mint
chocolate, and almond banana,
please!
68: Oh. She really DID order them all!
74:
Oh no! It's hit me—the overwhelming
sense of guilt!
79:
You get discouraged far too easily!
Allow ME to help you eat it all!
84: Huh? No way, this is mine!
90:
It's... so sweet, yet refreshingly cool...
It tastes like heaven!
94:
If that is to your liking, then I, the
magnanimous Inaho, will allow you
to have a bite of mine! Food is best
shared, after all.
99:
I-is it?! I've never heard of that!
Regardless, I'll have a taste!
105:
Inaho... Stella... This is simply too
much—gluttony is a vice, after all! Is
this really okay?
108:
It's okay. You're allowed to.
There's always room for dessert.
113:
Indeed! A dish this size is MEANT for
many people to partake in! We will
devour it in no time.
116:
We will take down the delicious,
mountainous foe before us by
working together! How inspirational!
120:
Fascinating... I've seen dango before,
but never ones where you can
choose your own filling like this!
124:
A piece of Yamato culture, altered...
for the better!
128:
Ooof... It looks... so appetizing...
Yet my stomach refuses its call!
137:
What are you talking about? With
sweets so expertly crafted right in
front of you, how can your appetite
NOT be whet?
140:
The spirit is willing... but the body... is
not...
145:
Delicious! It's incredible to be able to
make your own flavors!
148:
Say, what's our next destination? 
I read in the Oculus about a shop
that sells wonderful lemon pies!
151:
Oh, oh! Or... we could try out this
"Palpebra Parfait"! That sounds
wonderful too!
156:
W-wait... WAIT, I said!
My stomach... threatens to explode...
165:
I got carried away... It's just my habit,
you see. When I set my sights on
something, I can't look away.
170:
Haha! We should have known better
than to agree—you truly are a
bottomless pit, aren't you?
174:
But at least it seems you've gotten
over that which haunted you!
177:
How about also severing ties with
the troublesome organization that
forced those commandments onto
you?
183:
It was my wish to spend a wonderful
time like this with my friends.
185:
But I still love my work... Defeating
yokai, helping people, hearing their
words of thanks...
196:
Hehe. You want EVERYTHING, do you
not, Rengetsu? That is your nature!
199:
Maybe I don't... have to choose? 
I can just do... whatever I want?
202:
Yes... Perhaps there's no need to
make compromises.
205:
I... will return to Yamato, and to the
Spirit Hunt!
213:
I will change the Hunt, so that
people and yokai may come
together, and that I may help all
who are in need!
216:
You really ARE a greedy one,
wanting everything!
219:
But what about that irksome diviner
boy? What will he say?
223:
I... think he will want to put an end to
the Hunt.
225:
And that is understandable. But... to
leave all those people in the dark
just doesn't sit with me.
230: You wish to tell them the truth?
233:
Yes...
You're right, I DO wish for too much.
238:
Indeed! An insatiable, bottomless pit
of desires you are—one who has my
FULL support.
242:
Thank you, Inaho!
I will be on my way now!
246:
But first, another helping of dango,
to keep me going on the road!
